1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 21=

3
00:01:39,130 --> 00:01:41,770
Since the marriage has
irretrievably broken down,

4
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:43,570
let's move on

5
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:45,380
to the division of assets.

6
00:01:45,577 --> 00:01:46,770
Counsel for the defendant.

7
00:01:48,244 --> 00:01:50,555
(Authorized Representative)
There is an income gap between them.

8
00:01:50,570 --> 00:01:51,900
(Plaintiff)
However,

9
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:53,660
given the long duration of the marriage,

10
00:01:53,820 --> 00:01:56,490
we propose that my client retains
all stocks and liabilities.

11
00:01:56,620 --> 00:01:58,000
All cash assets,

12
00:01:58,088 --> 00:01:59,770
including bank deposits and investments,

13
00:01:59,770 --> 00:02:00,850
should be split fifty-fifty.

14
00:02:01,410 --> 00:02:03,900
As for the six real estate properties,
they should be divided

15
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:05,100
equally based on current value.

16
00:02:06,290 --> 00:02:07,130
Plaintiff?

17
00:02:08,220 --> 00:02:09,290
I don't agree.

18
00:02:09,450 --> 00:02:11,060
I want half the shares

19
00:02:11,060 --> 00:02:13,060
in both Aimei and Ronggang.

20
00:02:13,690 --> 00:02:14,690
As for those smaller ones

21
00:02:14,690 --> 00:02:16,290
and little ventures,

22
00:02:16,290 --> 00:02:17,290
I'm not interested.

23
00:02:18,066 --> 00:02:19,800
Authorized Representative
for the defendant.

24
00:02:19,820 --> 00:02:21,730
We oppose an equal split of the equity.

25
00:02:22,060 --> 00:02:23,380
Considering that my client

26
00:02:23,380 --> 00:02:25,340
has made immense
contributions to the firm...

27
00:02:25,890 --> 00:02:27,060
Did you hear that?

28
00:02:28,170 --> 00:02:30,410
I gave everything to that company.

29
00:02:30,410 --> 00:02:32,130
I'm the one who actually runs it!

30
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:33,780
You don't want a single small company,

31
00:02:34,660 --> 00:02:36,410
but you want half of the big ones?

32
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:38,290
Those are publicly traded companies.

33
00:02:38,290 --> 00:02:39,540
Do you even understand them?

34
00:02:39,540 --> 00:02:40,850
Why should you care?

35
00:02:41,260 --> 00:02:42,170
I'll have the money.

36
00:02:42,170 --> 00:02:43,260
I can hire consultants

37
00:02:43,260 --> 00:02:44,220
to come and work for me!

38
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:45,730
Work for you?

39
00:02:45,730 --> 00:02:46,890
(Courtroom 5, Camera 1)

40
00:02:46,890 --> 00:02:47,980
Do you have any idea

41
00:02:47,980 --> 00:02:49,130
how the modern economy works?

42
00:02:49,220 --> 00:02:50,890
Do you know what the stock market is?

43
00:02:50,890 --> 00:02:52,060
Mind your own business!

44
00:02:52,060 --> 00:02:54,190
The stock market isn't a supermarket!

45
00:02:54,260 --> 00:02:56,690
- Do you even have a trading account?
- Silence! That's enough.

46
00:02:56,690 --> 00:02:57,900
Go back and look after the kids.

47
00:02:57,911 --> 00:02:59,730
What business is it of yours?

48
00:02:59,730 --> 00:03:00,980
Watch your tones, both of you.

49
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:02,260
Control yourself.

50
00:03:02,780 --> 00:03:03,940
Please, control yourself.

51
00:03:06,010 --> 00:03:06,820
Fine.

52
00:03:07,380 --> 00:03:08,820
You're not budging on the shares.

53
00:03:09,044 --> 00:03:10,850
So, what exactly
are you willing to give me?

54
00:03:11,980 --> 00:03:13,010
Counsel for the defendant.

55
00:03:13,066 --> 00:03:15,422
The art gallery  in
the Economic Development Zone.

56
00:03:16,260 --> 00:03:17,340
An art gallery?

57
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:21,170
How much is the rent on that place?

58
00:03:21,422 --> 00:03:23,380
And what about
the maintenance and repairs?

59
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:25,570
(Art Gallery, EDZ, Tianhai City)
I don't even know what they sell there.

60
00:03:25,570 --> 00:03:26,730
They could be selling fakes.

61
00:03:26,730 --> 00:03:27,690
I'm clueless about that.

62
00:03:27,690 --> 00:03:30,130
You can always hire experts.

63
00:03:30,890 --> 00:03:32,980
Oh, so now you're okay
with me hiring experts?

64
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:34,260
Think about that gallery.

65
00:03:34,980 --> 00:03:36,610
Leasing agents, restoration experts,

66
00:03:36,610 --> 00:03:38,450
appraisers, auctioneers...

67
00:03:38,780 --> 00:03:39,940
Never mind the fees.

68
00:03:39,940 --> 00:03:41,060
That whole expert team

69
00:03:41,060 --> 00:03:42,940
is just a racket for scammers.

70
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:43,570
What?

71
00:03:43,570 --> 00:03:44,980
Didn't think I'd see through it?

72
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:45,888
You want me to sink

73
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:47,160
(Estimated annual revenue: 1.2 million)
my entire wealth into that pit.

74
00:03:47,170 --> 00:03:48,450
The gallery's annual revenue

75
00:03:48,450 --> 00:03:49,822
is actually quite substantial.

76
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:51,690
Forget it.

77
00:03:52,820 --> 00:03:53,940
She can take it or leave it.

78
00:03:55,450 --> 00:03:56,410
Ren Haiping.

79
00:03:57,450 --> 00:03:58,730
We were married for years.

80
00:03:58,940 --> 00:04:00,690
This isn't just about the money for me.

81
00:04:01,340 --> 00:04:02,260
Tell you what.

82
00:04:02,980 --> 00:04:04,010
You can keep the gallery,

83
00:04:04,130 --> 00:04:05,780
the equity, and the shares.

84
00:04:06,010 --> 00:04:07,340
You can keep those.

85
00:04:07,444 --> 00:04:08,730
But the rest of the real estate

86
00:04:09,060 --> 00:04:09,980
shall be mine.

87
00:04:11,450 --> 00:04:12,555
I can't give you the manor

88
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:13,850
in Junxiang Villa, Hainan.

89
00:04:13,850 --> 00:04:15,555
Mr. Zhang gave me
a major discount on that place.

90
00:04:15,622 --> 00:04:17,460
(Proof of Transaction Details)
We agreed that house

91
00:04:17,460 --> 00:04:18,460
would be for my retirement

92
00:04:18,460 --> 00:04:20,020
and Mr. Zhang's.

93
00:04:21,730 --> 00:04:22,540
Fine, then.

94
00:04:23,222 --> 00:04:24,730
But considering its market value...

95
00:04:24,730 --> 00:04:25,900
Enough.

96
00:04:27,050 --> 00:04:29,700
For the sake of our years together,
and since you have

97
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:31,170
custody of our three children,

98
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:32,810
whom you still have

99
00:04:32,810 --> 00:04:34,250
to provide for,

100
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:35,930
you can have the rest.

101
00:04:37,177 --> 00:04:38,866
Authorized Representative
for the defendant.

102
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:40,900
What exactly does the rest entail?

103
00:04:45,170 --> 00:04:46,980
A whole row of shops
in Qingcheng District.

104
00:04:47,220 --> 00:04:48,410
Two luxury apartments.

105
00:04:48,410 --> 00:04:49,540
Three villas.

106
00:04:49,660 --> 00:04:51,730
And a five-million-dollar deposit.

107
00:04:51,730 --> 00:04:53,490
With an annual interest rate
of 3.8 percent.

108
00:04:53,490 --> 00:04:54,490
It has been three years.

109
00:04:54,490 --> 00:04:56,555
The interest alone is
over five hundred thousand.

110
00:04:58,290 --> 00:04:59,460
I have truly been

111
00:04:59,460 --> 00:05:01,100
more than fair with you.

112
00:05:04,060 --> 00:05:05,100
(People's Court)

113
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:06,660
Tell Ms. Lou when you get back.

114
00:05:06,660 --> 00:05:08,980
Since she was the one who introduced us,

115
00:05:09,370 --> 00:05:10,460
I will definitely help her

116
00:05:10,660 --> 00:05:13,020
introduce her to Mr. Wang.

117
00:05:14,170 --> 00:05:16,370
Thank you for your appreciation
of her and the firm.

118
00:05:16,370 --> 00:05:17,370
You are very welcome.

119
00:05:19,980 --> 00:05:21,220
How are you getting home?

120
00:05:21,444 --> 00:05:23,290
I called for a ride,
but it is not here yet.

121
00:05:23,460 --> 00:05:24,490
Do not worry about that.

122
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:26,170
I will give you a ride. Jump in.

123
00:05:30,020 --> 00:05:32,170
I went through the files you sent over.

124
00:05:32,250 --> 00:05:33,955
Everything looks good for the most part.

125
00:05:34,044 --> 00:05:34,850
However,

126
00:05:35,020 --> 00:05:36,340
regarding the market section,

127
00:05:36,340 --> 00:05:37,850
you should double-check that with Wu.

128
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:39,050
What is that?

129
00:05:39,460 --> 00:05:40,460
It is settled.

130
00:05:41,540 --> 00:05:43,050
Everything was handled perfectly.

131
00:05:43,580 --> 00:05:45,170
The lawyer was very efficient.

132
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:48,020
Start the meeting.

133
00:05:48,020 --> 00:05:49,410
I am on my way back right now.

134
00:05:49,410 --> 00:05:50,410
I will be there soon.

135
00:05:51,490 --> 00:05:52,290
All right.

136
00:05:52,610 --> 00:05:53,540
Goodbye.

137
00:05:54,730 --> 00:05:55,660
Ms. Qin.

138
00:05:55,777 --> 00:05:57,660
How long have you been
with Ronghe Law Firm?

139
00:05:58,810 --> 00:05:59,900
Not very long.

140
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:01,780
I used to work for a firm

141
00:06:01,780 --> 00:06:03,700
that focused on cases
for the Family Court.

142
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:05,410
So you have only just joined?

143
00:06:05,780 --> 00:06:08,700
It sounds like you are really
carving out a niche for yourself.

144
00:06:11,980 --> 00:06:15,540
What exactly
does the Family Court handle?

145
00:06:15,540 --> 00:06:18,220
Is it just helping people
with divorce cases?

146
00:06:18,288 --> 00:06:20,290
Like, who gets the kids
or how they're cared for?

147
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:23,780
Besides divorces,
there's also asset division,

148
00:06:24,290 --> 00:06:26,730
alimony, and inheritance.

149
00:06:28,050 --> 00:06:30,700
Does inheritance fall
under the Family Court, too?

150
00:06:32,490 --> 00:06:33,490
I think court fees

151
00:06:33,490 --> 00:06:34,810
for inheritance cases

152
00:06:34,810 --> 00:06:36,930
depend on the value of the claim.

153
00:06:36,930 --> 00:06:37,780
Is that right?

154
00:06:38,340 --> 00:06:38,900
Yes.

155
00:06:38,900 --> 00:06:40,170
The court sets its fees

156
00:06:40,220 --> 00:06:42,220
based on the claim's standard value.

157
00:06:42,700 --> 00:06:43,780
As for law firms,

158
00:06:43,780 --> 00:06:45,610
each has its own set of standards.

159
00:06:48,610 --> 00:06:49,660
Ms. Qin.

160
00:06:50,810 --> 00:06:52,050
I've got an idea

161
00:06:52,050 --> 00:06:53,700
that I'd like to discuss with you.

162
00:06:54,170 --> 00:06:55,100
I'm listening.

163
00:06:55,170 --> 00:06:56,170
I'll provide the funding

164
00:06:56,660 --> 00:06:58,580
to help you open your own law firm.

165
00:06:58,980 --> 00:07:01,250
Don't worry about finding clients.
I'll handle that.

166
00:07:01,250 --> 00:07:02,370
And I can promise you

167
00:07:02,370 --> 00:07:04,730
that every case will be
worth at least ten million.

168
00:07:04,980 --> 00:07:07,140
If you charge
two hundred thousand per case,

169
00:07:07,140 --> 00:07:08,610
and you do ten cases a year,

170
00:07:08,610 --> 00:07:10,370
just do the math on what you'd earn.

171
00:07:12,810 --> 00:07:14,140
If ten cases aren't enough,

172
00:07:14,900 --> 00:07:15,980
then make it twenty.

173
00:07:16,355 --> 00:07:18,370
As long as you're up for it,
you can take them on.

174
00:07:19,290 --> 00:07:20,340
How's your English?

175
00:07:20,340 --> 00:07:21,933
Ever handled international litigation?

176
00:07:24,250 --> 00:07:25,900
Asset division cases

177
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:27,050
can be long or short.

178
00:07:27,050 --> 00:07:28,290
If things go smoothly,

179
00:07:28,580 --> 00:07:30,100
it might be settled very quickly.

180
00:07:30,170 --> 00:07:31,290
But if they don't,

181
00:07:31,290 --> 00:07:33,780
it's possible they won't end for years.

182
00:07:34,340 --> 00:07:35,460
But Ronghe is a major firm.

183
00:07:35,460 --> 00:07:37,980
I'm talking about
working with you personally.

184
00:07:40,540 --> 00:07:41,540
What is it?

185
00:07:41,780 --> 00:07:44,490
Are you worried
I'm testing you for your boss?

186
00:07:45,460 --> 00:07:46,900
There's really no need for that.

187
00:07:48,660 --> 00:07:50,290
The truth is, I'm still quite young

188
00:07:50,290 --> 00:07:51,700
and I lack the experience.

189
00:07:52,020 --> 00:07:54,170
I don't think
this role is a good fit for me.

190
00:07:54,170 --> 00:07:57,020
That won't stop you
from working at Ronghe.

191
00:07:57,850 --> 00:07:59,730
You can manage both at once.

192
00:08:01,370 --> 00:08:02,540
We'll run the business

193
00:08:02,610 --> 00:08:05,250
as a consulting firm.

194
00:08:05,810 --> 00:08:06,980
I'll provide the capital,

195
00:08:07,050 --> 00:08:08,140
and you provide the talent.

196
00:08:08,490 --> 00:08:09,250
How about it?

197
00:08:11,810 --> 00:08:12,730
We're here?

198
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:15,660
Ms. Qin, this is my stop.

199
00:08:15,730 --> 00:08:16,850
I've got a meeting upstairs.

200
00:08:16,850 --> 00:08:18,555
He'll drive you back
to Ronghe Law Firm.

201
00:08:18,850 --> 00:08:19,700
Thank you.

202
00:08:23,170 --> 00:08:24,250
Ms. Qin.

203
00:08:25,422 --> 00:08:26,850
I'll be waiting for your word.

204
00:08:43,850 --> 00:08:44,820
Excuse me,

205
00:08:44,933 --> 00:08:46,488
could you pull over for a second?

206
00:08:48,010 --> 00:08:48,890
Mr. Ren.

207
00:08:49,700 --> 00:08:50,490
Mr. Ren.

208
00:08:51,770 --> 00:08:52,770
I'm sorry.

209
00:08:53,490 --> 00:08:55,580
I gave it some more thought just now.

210
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:58,850
I really value the chance
to learn at Ronghe Law Firm.

211
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:01,580
I need to stay there
for a few more years.

212
00:09:01,580 --> 00:09:02,700
But I'm truly grateful

213
00:09:02,700 --> 00:09:04,460
for your confidence in me.

214
00:09:04,650 --> 00:09:05,850
I just don't think

215
00:09:05,850 --> 00:09:07,770
I'm ready to run a law firm

216
00:09:07,850 --> 00:09:09,100
on my own yet.

217
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:13,250
I understand.

218
00:09:14,060 --> 00:09:16,490
Come find me

219
00:09:16,980 --> 00:09:18,100
whenever you're ready.

220
00:09:22,850 --> 00:09:23,820
Thank you.

221
00:09:26,610 --> 00:09:27,650
Don't mention it.

222
00:09:38,770 --> 00:09:39,250
Judge Shen.

223
00:09:39,250 --> 00:09:41,220
I've been wanting
to try this place forever.

224
00:09:41,420 --> 00:09:42,770
Everyone's been raving about it.

225
00:09:43,340 --> 00:09:44,420
It's just

226
00:09:45,730 --> 00:09:47,060
around that corner.

227
00:09:47,180 --> 00:09:48,250
I already checked the menu.

228
00:09:48,250 --> 00:09:49,730
Watch it. Slow down.

229
00:09:50,300 --> 00:09:51,770
I'll order us some great stuff.

230
00:09:51,770 --> 00:09:52,610
Xianghui,

231
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:54,010
let's eat at that one.

232
00:09:54,444 --> 00:09:56,460
Wait, I already made
a reservation over there.

233
00:09:57,460 --> 00:09:58,370
Change it.

234
00:09:59,850 --> 00:10:01,300
That place is better.

235
00:10:01,530 --> 00:10:02,700
Which one do you like?

236
00:10:03,420 --> 00:10:04,580
Out of these...

237
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:06,700
This one.

238
00:10:06,700 --> 00:10:07,850
Send me this one.

239
00:10:08,180 --> 00:10:08,820
Okay.

240
00:10:08,890 --> 00:10:10,610
This looks so silly.

241
00:10:10,688 --> 00:10:11,250
Look at this.

242
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:12,250
He's toast.

243
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:14,100
He'll be calling me "Boss" all semester.

244
00:10:14,220 --> 00:10:15,010
Really?

245
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:16,940
There's more. Check out these nice ones.

246
00:10:17,311 --> 00:10:18,940
Let's see what your sister ordered.

247
00:10:19,130 --> 00:10:20,610
Taro mochi or mango cheese tea.

248
00:10:20,688 --> 00:10:21,644
Which one do you want?

249
00:10:21,688 --> 00:10:22,220
I want both.

250
00:10:22,530 --> 00:10:23,370
You little rascal.

251
00:10:23,370 --> 00:10:24,820
You're not leaving any for me?

252
00:10:24,850 --> 00:10:25,980
Pick one. Just one.

253
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:28,530
I want them both.

254
00:10:29,980 --> 00:10:30,610
Fine.

255
00:10:30,610 --> 00:10:31,420
What about mine?

256
00:10:31,420 --> 00:10:32,800
Just let me have a sip later.

257
00:10:32,940 --> 00:10:33,890
Did you get me anything?

258
00:10:34,060 --> 00:10:35,130
I forgot.

259
00:10:39,370 --> 00:10:40,700
Let's take a photo.

260
00:10:41,010 --> 00:10:41,850
Come on.

261
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:43,420
- Thank you.
- Enjoy your food.

262
00:10:43,490 --> 00:10:45,180
One, two, three.

263
00:10:49,580 --> 00:10:50,610
Have a look.

264
00:10:51,530 --> 00:10:52,340
Is it good?

265
00:10:52,340 --> 00:10:53,300
This shot looks good.

266
00:10:55,250 --> 00:10:56,100
(As it turns out,)

267
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:57,770
(a single fork in the road)

268
00:10:57,940 --> 00:11:00,700
(was enough to trap two families
and three generations)

269
00:11:00,770 --> 00:11:02,530
(in a whirlpool of love and hate)

270
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:04,420
(for decades.)

271
00:11:04,820 --> 00:11:06,490
(Behind all that chaos,)

272
00:11:06,730 --> 00:11:07,730
(maybe they were missing)

273
00:11:07,730 --> 00:11:09,600
(a chance to clear up
a misunderstanding.)

274
00:11:09,730 --> 00:11:11,420
(When all the rights and wrongs)

275
00:11:11,490 --> 00:11:13,820
(finally settle in court,)

276
00:11:14,180 --> 00:11:17,010
(the real wounds
are still far from healing.)

277
00:11:17,650 --> 00:11:20,180
(The law can hand down a fair verdict,)

278
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:22,730
(but it can't pay back stolen time.)

279
00:11:23,250 --> 00:11:24,980
(It can't mend the hearts torn apart)

280
00:11:24,980 --> 00:11:27,180
(by the bonds of blood and upbringing.)

281
00:11:27,650 --> 00:11:28,940
(That's when you understand)

282
00:11:28,940 --> 00:11:31,580
(why the purpose of mediation.)

283
00:11:31,650 --> 00:11:33,940
(It's sometimes
more important than a final ruling.)

284
00:11:34,370 --> 00:11:35,730
(A judge's responsibility)

285
00:11:35,730 --> 00:11:38,530
(might just be to search
through these emotional ruins,)

286
00:11:38,730 --> 00:11:43,100
(looking down
to carefully guard that tiny spark)

287
00:11:43,250 --> 00:11:44,770
(of humanity before it's gone.)

288
00:11:45,130 --> 00:11:47,700
(Can we provide impartial justice
without being cold)

289
00:11:48,220 --> 00:11:49,940
(while also finding a home)

290
00:11:50,180 --> 00:11:52,010
(for those broken ties?)

291
00:11:52,130 --> 00:11:54,420
(One that's flawed
but still full of warmth?)

292
00:11:56,890 --> 00:11:57,940
Eat up, Judge Shen.

293
00:11:58,850 --> 00:11:59,890
The gloves are right there.

294
00:12:00,370 --> 00:12:01,300
It's pretty good.

295
00:12:01,530 --> 00:12:02,370
Good.

296
00:12:10,130 --> 00:12:11,250
Ms. Qin.

297
00:12:11,490 --> 00:12:12,610
It's been a while.

298
00:12:12,820 --> 00:12:14,060
What've you been up to lately?

299
00:12:14,420 --> 00:12:15,650
I've got a new job.

300
00:12:15,890 --> 00:12:17,820
It should be at some top-tier law firm.

301
00:12:17,890 --> 00:12:19,850
You're practically glowing.

302
00:12:20,180 --> 00:12:21,370
Still as sweet as ever, I see.

303
00:12:22,180 --> 00:12:23,420
We've got plenty of new items.

304
00:12:23,420 --> 00:12:24,490
Want to give them a try?

305
00:12:27,730 --> 00:12:28,400
No, thank you.

306
00:12:28,420 --> 00:12:29,820
I'll stick with the usual. A coffee...

307
00:12:29,820 --> 00:12:31,220
With double sugar and double cream.

308
00:12:31,610 --> 00:12:32,850
Look at how smart I am.

309
00:12:32,933 --> 00:12:34,420
I'm just waiting for you to get famous,

310
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:36,130
so the press'll come interview me.

311
00:12:37,940 --> 00:12:39,370
Then I guess I'd better work harder.

312
00:12:39,490 --> 00:12:40,580
You're almost there.

313
00:12:40,730 --> 00:12:41,980
I remember you saying

314
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:43,490
that when you finally made it big,

315
00:12:43,580 --> 00:12:45,180
you'd order every single dessert

316
00:12:45,180 --> 00:12:46,420
we had.

317
00:12:46,420 --> 00:12:48,100
You'd have yourself a real feast.

318
00:12:49,100 --> 00:12:51,490
Today, most of our treats
are ten percent off.

319
00:12:51,490 --> 00:12:52,490
Want to try some?

320
00:12:52,610 --> 00:12:54,066
Were you eavesdropping on me?

321
00:12:55,340 --> 00:12:56,180
Tell you what.

322
00:12:56,250 --> 00:12:57,530
Whatever's ten percent off,

323
00:12:57,530 --> 00:12:58,730
I'll take two of everything.

324
00:12:59,650 --> 00:13:00,460
For real?

325
00:13:00,820 --> 00:13:02,300
I'm just kidding.

326
00:13:02,610 --> 00:13:03,850
Well, I'm not.

327
00:13:03,850 --> 00:13:05,340
I'll take them back for my colleagues.

328
00:13:05,420 --> 00:13:05,850
All right.

329
00:13:05,850 --> 00:13:07,490
Give me a second and I'll pack them up.

330
00:13:10,940 --> 00:13:11,820
(Busy?)

331
00:13:11,940 --> 00:13:13,220
(Come out for a coffee.)

332
00:13:41,850 --> 00:13:44,460
(I could probably slack off for a bit.)

333
00:13:44,610 --> 00:13:46,300
(But your firm is way too far from me.)

334
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:47,911
(In the time it'd take to get there.)

335
00:13:47,977 --> 00:13:49,444
(I could've finished an autopsy report.)

336
00:13:49,488 --> 00:13:50,530
(Actually, it's very close.)

337
00:13:50,530 --> 00:13:51,850
(It's right across from the court.)

338
00:13:51,850 --> 00:13:53,088
(Wait for me. I'll be right there.)

339
00:13:53,133 --> 00:13:53,980
(Okay.)

340
00:14:02,940 --> 00:14:03,940
Judge Shen?

341
00:14:05,220 --> 00:14:06,820
It really is you! What a coincidence.

342
00:14:06,820 --> 00:14:08,010
I brought Guo out to play,

343
00:14:08,010 --> 00:14:09,288
and I thought it looked like you.

344
00:14:09,420 --> 00:14:10,650
It's a small world.

345
00:14:10,820 --> 00:14:11,730
There he is.

346
00:14:11,980 --> 00:14:12,890
Mrs. Liu.

347
00:14:13,940 --> 00:14:15,420
Why don't we sit down and talk?

348
00:14:15,940 --> 00:14:16,890
Is this a good time?

349
00:14:16,890 --> 00:14:18,010
Of course.

350
00:14:24,220 --> 00:14:25,650
So, is Xiaosheng

351
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:27,010
willing to come home with you yet?

352
00:14:28,850 --> 00:14:29,850
Not yet.

353
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:32,610
There was a debate at school today,

354
00:14:33,250 --> 00:14:34,530
and parents were allowed to watch.

355
00:14:35,010 --> 00:14:37,300
The other family said they were busy
and couldn't make it.

356
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:39,130
Guo reached out to us,

357
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:40,890
and Qiao took some time off work.

358
00:14:40,980 --> 00:14:42,820
We came here to be his cheerleaders.

359
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:44,610
Have the two of you

360
00:14:45,370 --> 00:14:46,730
been seeing each other since then?

361
00:14:46,770 --> 00:14:48,940
He was pretty resistant at first.

362
00:14:49,700 --> 00:14:51,940
But then, he added Qiao on WeChat.

363
00:14:52,530 --> 00:14:54,340
They're siblings, after all.

364
00:14:54,650 --> 00:14:56,220
The more they chat, the closer they get.

365
00:14:57,610 --> 00:14:58,610
In this past month,

366
00:14:59,100 --> 00:15:00,530
we've actually met up quite a lot.

367
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:04,300
Today

368
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:06,610
was the first time
he brought us to his school.

369
00:15:09,370 --> 00:15:10,980
He introduced us to his classmates.

370
00:15:15,650 --> 00:15:18,100
"This is my grandma and my sister."

371
00:15:22,820 --> 00:15:23,820
Oh, I'm sorry.

372
00:15:23,980 --> 00:15:25,700
That's wonderful news.

373
00:15:38,850 --> 00:15:39,940
The tofu is ready.

374
00:15:40,650 --> 00:15:41,650
Smells good, doesn't it?

375
00:15:42,340 --> 00:15:43,650
It looks delicious.

376
00:15:46,420 --> 00:15:48,340
I really have to thank you for this.

377
00:15:50,300 --> 00:15:51,580
I'm just glad I could help.

378
00:15:51,580 --> 00:15:53,010
As long as both sides give a little,

379
00:15:53,030 --> 00:15:54,180
there's room for a compromise.

380
00:15:54,180 --> 00:15:55,060
Anyway,

381
00:15:55,130 --> 00:15:57,180
I'm sure time will tell.

382
00:16:05,250 --> 00:16:06,340
I'm curious.

383
00:16:07,010 --> 00:16:09,340
What do you look like
when you're feeling smug?

384
00:16:17,460 --> 00:16:18,420
Sorry, I'm late.

385
00:16:20,610 --> 00:16:22,820
My god, that's a lot of cake.

386
00:16:23,060 --> 00:16:24,250
Are these all for me?

387
00:16:24,490 --> 00:16:26,180
It's to thank you for taking care of me.

388
00:16:26,370 --> 00:16:27,340
This isn't nearly enough.

389
00:16:27,530 --> 00:16:29,420
I should've prepared
a real feast for you.

390
00:16:29,650 --> 00:16:31,300
These are all your favorites.

391
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:32,700
Two of each.

392
00:16:33,250 --> 00:16:34,340
I guess it was worth it.

393
00:16:35,370 --> 00:16:36,530
Okay, fess up.

394
00:16:36,980 --> 00:16:38,940
Why'd you suddenly think of coming here?

395
00:16:39,890 --> 00:16:40,820
I...

396
00:16:42,511 --> 00:16:43,980
I happened to have a case nearby,

397
00:16:44,130 --> 00:16:45,370
so I stopped in.

398
00:16:46,580 --> 00:16:47,650
Give me a break.

399
00:16:47,850 --> 00:16:49,100
Have you ever heard the saying?

400
00:16:49,180 --> 00:16:51,940
Success is no fun if you're hiding it.

401
00:16:52,460 --> 00:16:54,940
You didn't come
all this way just for cake.

402
00:16:55,250 --> 00:16:56,340
Who are you waiting for?

403
00:16:57,850 --> 00:16:59,650
What are you talking about?

404
00:17:04,770 --> 00:17:05,620
What?

405
00:17:06,090 --> 00:17:07,770
You aren't eating?

406
00:17:07,940 --> 00:17:08,860
I...

407
00:17:09,620 --> 00:17:10,700
I'm not really used to it.

408
00:17:11,570 --> 00:17:14,050
When I look at
these pretty little cakes,

409
00:17:14,420 --> 00:17:15,460
they look like

410
00:17:17,010 --> 00:17:18,620
dreamy little bubbles.

411
00:17:18,940 --> 00:17:20,050
Little bubbles?

412
00:17:20,980 --> 00:17:21,860
Look.

413
00:17:22,570 --> 00:17:24,250
We used to stress over rent,

414
00:17:24,730 --> 00:17:25,810
finding a hot meal,

415
00:17:26,220 --> 00:17:27,570
and my grandma's medical bills.

416
00:17:28,290 --> 00:17:29,420
I was constantly anxious.

417
00:17:29,810 --> 00:17:31,220
I had so many problems to deal with.

418
00:17:33,290 --> 00:17:34,900
Now that everything is settled,

419
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:37,090
it just feels

420
00:17:37,730 --> 00:17:38,860
surreal.

421
00:17:39,980 --> 00:17:41,140
It's as if

422
00:17:41,140 --> 00:17:42,770
there are these dreamy little bubbles.

423
00:17:44,250 --> 00:17:46,250
I'm just afraid that if I'm not careful,

424
00:17:47,090 --> 00:17:48,220
they'll all burst.

425
00:17:49,666 --> 00:17:51,250
I'm worried that with one wrong move,

426
00:17:51,770 --> 00:17:52,900
I'll pop them.

427
00:17:56,530 --> 00:17:57,730
So what if they pop?

428
00:17:57,900 --> 00:17:59,250
Let them burst.

429
00:17:59,980 --> 00:18:01,660
Out with the old and in with the new.

430
00:18:02,010 --> 00:18:03,010
Besides,

431
00:18:03,530 --> 00:18:05,700
it's about time you blew a new bubble.

432
00:18:05,730 --> 00:18:07,133
Have a little ambition, will you?

433
00:18:07,290 --> 00:18:08,490
What new bubble?

434
00:18:09,570 --> 00:18:12,050
Blow a bigger and rounder one.

435
00:18:13,140 --> 00:18:15,180
Can't we set a new goal for once?

436
00:18:16,010 --> 00:18:17,010
Find a new one.

437
00:18:17,180 --> 00:18:19,900
Then you can hire me
to be your assistant.

438
00:18:20,866 --> 00:18:22,980
You're a forensic doctor.
Why would I hire you?

439
00:18:23,940 --> 00:18:25,570
Also, what kind of trouble would I be in

440
00:18:25,730 --> 00:18:27,250
to need you to get rid of the evidence?

441
00:18:28,290 --> 00:18:31,220
Pouring water to cool down
the money counter.

442
00:18:42,420 --> 00:18:43,570
Still feeling melancholy?

443
00:18:48,940 --> 00:18:50,330
Is it because of

444
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:53,860
that pink,

445
00:18:54,140 --> 00:18:57,530
dreamy love bubble?

446
00:18:58,620 --> 00:18:59,770
That's so corny.

447
00:19:01,660 --> 00:19:02,900
That's all in the past.

448
00:19:03,860 --> 00:19:05,044
It's Crazy Thursday today.

449
00:19:05,111 --> 00:19:06,133
Desserts are on sale.

450
00:19:06,555 --> 00:19:08,140
Do you want me to bring anything back?

451
00:19:08,330 --> 00:19:09,220
Le?

452
00:19:10,620 --> 00:19:11,090
Hold on.

453
00:19:11,090 --> 00:19:11,810
Hi.

454
00:19:11,940 --> 00:19:13,530
Can you write this down for me?

455
00:19:13,860 --> 00:19:15,570
A tiramisu for Ms. Shu.

456
00:19:16,700 --> 00:19:18,010
Does Judge Shen need anything?

457
00:19:19,460 --> 00:19:20,380
Okay.

458
00:19:20,660 --> 00:19:21,730
For you,

459
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:24,140
the additive-free low-sugar sponge cake.

460
00:19:25,010 --> 00:19:25,980
What about Aixi?

461
00:19:28,010 --> 00:19:29,860
Does she just want the avocado yogurt?

462
00:19:30,730 --> 00:19:32,220
Got it. Thirty percent sugar.

463
00:19:33,770 --> 00:19:34,770
How about Xianghui?

464
00:19:36,730 --> 00:19:37,860
You got it.

465
00:19:42,090 --> 00:19:43,660
(I haven't seen him in ages.)

466
00:19:43,888 --> 00:19:45,530
(I wonder if everything's going okay.)

467
00:19:48,220 --> 00:19:50,330
That pink little love bubble

468
00:19:50,810 --> 00:19:53,900
that'll never burst.

469
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:56,540
♪All the little things♪

470
00:19:56,540 --> 00:19:58,880
♪Between you and me♪

471
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:01,650
♪Woven into our lives♪

472
00:20:02,420 --> 00:20:04,350
♪The building blocks of life♪

473
00:20:04,350 --> 00:20:06,120
♪Shape the sky above us♪

474
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:08,310
♪Are you doing alright?♪

475
00:20:08,610 --> 00:20:11,520
♪What are you struggling for?♪

476
00:20:12,130 --> 00:20:13,950
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

477
00:20:14,733 --> 00:20:15,810
It's meant for the vomiting.

478
00:20:16,420 --> 00:20:17,570
Let me try some.

479
00:20:17,570 --> 00:20:20,720
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

480
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:24,670
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

481
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:25,530
Delicious, right?

482
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:28,990
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

483
00:20:28,990 --> 00:20:33,820
(Case closed)

484
00:20:33,820 --> 00:20:37,580
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

485
00:20:37,580 --> 00:20:39,260
(Report for duty)

486
00:20:39,260 --> 00:20:41,910
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

487
00:20:41,910 --> 00:20:42,940
Shen Xiezhi.

488
00:20:44,220 --> 00:20:45,220
Let's date.

489
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:47,620
I mean,

490
00:20:49,050 --> 00:20:50,290
let's be together.

491
00:20:51,660 --> 00:20:53,140
But we still haven't bridged

492
00:20:53,140 --> 00:20:54,380
that gap between us.

493
00:20:55,380 --> 00:20:56,980
I might head to the High Court,

494
00:20:57,980 --> 00:20:59,490
and you're going to a top-tier law firm.

495
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:01,380
(I heard a judge was seconded
to Beijing and you were the backup pick.)

496
00:21:01,380 --> 00:21:02,688
The selection results are out.

497
00:21:03,420 --> 00:21:04,700
I got the position.

498
00:21:07,960 --> 00:21:10,180
♪Where fairness stands♪

499
00:21:10,180 --> 00:21:11,900
(Report for duty)

500
00:21:11,900 --> 00:21:14,760
♪Within every heart♪

501
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:16,570
Come in.

502
00:21:18,660 --> 00:21:19,860
You should eat first.

503
00:21:19,940 --> 00:21:21,490
I'll just email you the file later.

504
00:21:21,490 --> 00:21:22,660
No need. It's fine.

505
00:21:22,900 --> 00:21:24,420
Come here and tell me about it.

506
00:21:34,620 --> 00:21:35,940
Regarding the division of assets,

507
00:21:35,940 --> 00:21:37,940
Mr. Ren and Ms. Bai made a decision.

508
00:21:38,250 --> 00:21:40,220
The court used a summary procedure
to wrap it up.

509
00:21:40,420 --> 00:21:42,770
Mr. Ren was very pleased
with the outcome.

510
00:21:43,460 --> 00:21:44,460
Nicely done.

511
00:21:45,140 --> 00:21:45,700
Right.

512
00:21:45,810 --> 00:21:46,888
Mr. Ren said he's willing

513
00:21:46,955 --> 00:21:48,730
to introduce you to Mr. Wang.

514
00:21:49,460 --> 00:21:50,420
Are you sure?

515
00:21:51,620 --> 00:21:52,490
That's fantastic.

516
00:21:52,620 --> 00:21:55,250
I was planning to go dig through
Mr. Wang's trash this afternoon.

517
00:21:55,660 --> 00:21:56,900
You're coming with me next time.

518
00:21:57,220 --> 00:21:58,530
This counts as a win for you.

519
00:21:59,420 --> 00:22:00,420
Thank you, Ms. Lou.

520
00:22:03,290 --> 00:22:03,980
Something else?

521
00:22:04,660 --> 00:22:06,620
Actually, Mr. Ren mentioned today

522
00:22:06,860 --> 00:22:08,533
that he'd fund a new company for me.

523
00:22:09,940 --> 00:22:11,220
Then I should warn you.

524
00:22:11,530 --> 00:22:13,460
If he offers you money to start a firm,

525
00:22:13,810 --> 00:22:14,900
you have to turn him down.

526
00:22:15,180 --> 00:22:16,330
I already did.

527
00:22:16,490 --> 00:22:18,220
I've only just joined Ronghe Law Firm,

528
00:22:18,220 --> 00:22:20,288
so I want to stay
and learn for a few years.

529
00:22:20,860 --> 00:22:22,460
I've heard that Mr. Ren is moving

530
00:22:22,700 --> 00:22:25,380
a massive amount of assets overseas.

531
00:22:25,860 --> 00:22:27,050
If you get caught up in that,

532
00:22:27,140 --> 00:22:29,140
it could destroy
your professional future.

533
00:22:29,290 --> 00:22:30,380
So you noticed it, too?

534
00:22:30,730 --> 00:22:32,090
That's what I wanted to tell you.

535
00:22:32,220 --> 00:22:33,620
Because of all that movement,

536
00:22:33,810 --> 00:22:36,420
I suspect he and Ms. Bai
are having a sham divorce.

537
00:22:37,860 --> 00:22:39,010
Do you have any proof?

538
00:22:39,010 --> 00:22:40,220
It's just a hunch.

539
00:22:40,460 --> 00:22:41,900
But I think that independent

540
00:22:41,900 --> 00:22:43,570
director compensation case spooks him.

541
00:22:43,688 --> 00:22:44,770
He's getting ahead of it.

542
00:22:44,844 --> 00:22:46,488
He's transferring everything to his wife

543
00:22:46,510 --> 00:22:48,733
before he's targeted.

544
00:22:48,770 --> 00:22:50,570
It looks like he's keeping

545
00:22:50,620 --> 00:22:51,770
all the valuable for himself.

546
00:22:51,860 --> 00:22:54,140
Like the physical businesses
and the company equity.

547
00:22:54,530 --> 00:22:55,530
But in reality,

548
00:22:55,530 --> 00:22:57,900
the real wealth is
the property in Tianhai City

549
00:22:57,900 --> 00:22:59,330
and the cash in the bank.

550
00:22:59,570 --> 00:23:01,010
If the company implodes,

551
00:23:01,010 --> 00:23:02,900
the fallout'll be catastrophic.

552
00:23:04,620 --> 00:23:05,530
This is the only piece

553
00:23:05,530 --> 00:23:07,620
of real estate he kept.

554
00:23:08,010 --> 00:23:09,810
So you're saying

555
00:23:10,380 --> 00:23:11,570
it's all just an act?

556
00:23:11,940 --> 00:23:12,860
The uglier it gets,

557
00:23:12,860 --> 00:23:14,090
the more convincing it looks.

558
00:23:14,420 --> 00:23:15,330
If things go south

559
00:23:15,420 --> 00:23:17,090
for Mr. Ren later,

560
00:23:17,570 --> 00:23:18,490
he won't be accused

561
00:23:18,490 --> 00:23:20,860
of a fraudulent transfer of assets.

562
00:23:21,010 --> 00:23:22,860
He's a brilliant economist.

563
00:23:22,940 --> 00:23:24,570
I don't believe for a second

564
00:23:24,570 --> 00:23:26,290
that he'd just hand over all his

565
00:23:26,290 --> 00:23:28,140
cold, hard cash
to his wife in a divorce.

566
00:23:28,180 --> 00:23:29,660
It's all speculation.

567
00:23:30,090 --> 00:23:31,420
Mr. Ren is fine for now.

568
00:23:32,010 --> 00:23:33,010
If he wants a divorce

569
00:23:33,180 --> 00:23:34,980
and wants to give his wife assets,

570
00:23:34,980 --> 00:23:36,330
even a judge can't touch that.

571
00:23:37,660 --> 00:23:39,860
But once the company fails,

572
00:23:40,010 --> 00:23:40,900
the creditors'll be

573
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:42,700
left holding the bag.

574
00:23:42,770 --> 00:23:45,250
That's no longer a lawyer's concern.

575
00:23:47,730 --> 00:23:48,380
I know.

576
00:23:48,380 --> 00:23:50,220
But I've still got
a bad feeling about this.

577
00:23:50,860 --> 00:23:52,250
Because during the hearing,

578
00:23:52,250 --> 00:23:53,490
a lot of his decisions

579
00:23:53,810 --> 00:23:55,530
didn't match what we'd discussed.

580
00:23:55,530 --> 00:23:57,490
Plus, if this gets out of hand,

581
00:23:57,980 --> 00:23:59,050
the public backlash

582
00:23:59,140 --> 00:24:01,570
could hit Ronghe Law Firm, too.

583
00:24:02,730 --> 00:24:04,620
I'm glad you're looking
at the bigger picture.

584
00:24:06,090 --> 00:24:07,090
Qin Rui,

585
00:24:07,490 --> 00:24:09,420
you handled divorces
at your old storefront,

586
00:24:09,570 --> 00:24:10,866
and you're handling them here.

587
00:24:10,888 --> 00:24:12,380
It's the same thing.

588
00:24:12,770 --> 00:24:13,900
Same court appearances,

589
00:24:14,010 --> 00:24:15,250
same asset divisions,

590
00:24:15,250 --> 00:24:16,660
and applying the same laws.

591
00:24:17,420 --> 00:24:18,940
So why are the stakes

592
00:24:19,460 --> 00:24:21,050
and the legal fees so different?

593
00:24:24,010 --> 00:24:25,250
When the amount at stake

594
00:24:25,250 --> 00:24:26,940
reaches a certain scale,

595
00:24:27,220 --> 00:24:30,250
the people, the interests,

596
00:24:30,250 --> 00:24:32,250
the risks, and the tactics involved

597
00:24:32,330 --> 00:24:33,620
all go up with it.

598
00:24:34,220 --> 00:24:35,380
If you're skilled enough

599
00:24:35,380 --> 00:24:37,810
to maximize a client's interests

600
00:24:37,940 --> 00:24:39,900
while spotting every risk,

601
00:24:40,050 --> 00:24:41,250
resisting temptation,

602
00:24:41,250 --> 00:24:42,490
and knowing how to react,

603
00:24:42,620 --> 00:24:44,380
then you've earned that paycheck.

604
00:24:44,770 --> 00:24:46,570
Think of your old cases

605
00:24:46,570 --> 00:24:48,050
as regular hunting.

606
00:24:48,290 --> 00:24:50,140
Now, you're hunting in a minefield.

607
00:24:50,380 --> 00:24:51,490
You can't lose the prey,

608
00:24:51,770 --> 00:24:53,700
but you've also got to stay alive.

609
00:24:56,940 --> 00:24:57,860
I understand.

610
00:25:32,730 --> 00:25:33,730
What's wrong?

611
00:25:33,900 --> 00:25:35,050
What's happened, my lady?

612
00:25:37,490 --> 00:25:39,330
Talk to me. What is it?

613
00:25:39,940 --> 00:25:40,810
I'm done for.

614
00:25:40,940 --> 00:25:42,460
I'm done. It's over. It's totally over.

615
00:25:43,290 --> 00:25:44,380
Just now,

616
00:25:44,700 --> 00:25:46,010
I wanted to use the air freshener,

617
00:25:46,010 --> 00:25:47,330
but I grabbed the wrong one.

618
00:25:47,490 --> 00:25:49,050
I used the bug spray by mistake.

619
00:25:50,180 --> 00:25:51,220
What do I do?

620
00:25:51,220 --> 00:25:53,570
The doctor already said the baby

621
00:25:53,860 --> 00:25:55,730
wasn't developing well
during the checkup.

622
00:25:55,730 --> 00:25:57,311
This is going to make it even worse.

623
00:25:57,355 --> 00:25:59,140
Should we go to the hospital?

624
00:25:59,460 --> 00:26:00,730
Let's go. Right now. Come on.

625
00:26:00,730 --> 00:26:01,490
Okay.

626
00:26:01,490 --> 00:26:02,490
What happened, Le?

627
00:26:02,860 --> 00:26:03,700
What's going on?

628
00:26:03,980 --> 00:26:04,940
Mom,

629
00:26:05,330 --> 00:26:06,860
I'm so sorry.

630
00:26:07,140 --> 00:26:08,220
I just...

631
00:26:08,290 --> 00:26:09,220
I accidentally

632
00:26:09,220 --> 00:26:11,220
inhaled some bug spray.

633
00:26:11,330 --> 00:26:12,980
It's definitely going to hurt the baby.

634
00:26:14,330 --> 00:26:15,770
Do you feel sick right now?

635
00:26:15,770 --> 00:26:17,010
Yes, I feel sick!

636
00:26:17,090 --> 00:26:18,490
Everything feels wrong.

637
00:26:18,490 --> 00:26:19,090
Let's go.

638
00:26:19,090 --> 00:26:20,530
I'm dizzy, too.

639
00:26:20,980 --> 00:26:22,570
Everything hurts.

640
00:26:23,220 --> 00:26:25,220
Bug spray? It's fine.

641
00:26:25,220 --> 00:26:26,250
Mom!

642
00:26:26,420 --> 00:26:27,420
Do you really think

643
00:26:27,700 --> 00:26:29,220
I am that irresponsible?

644
00:26:29,330 --> 00:26:30,530
Ever since you got pregnant,

645
00:26:30,620 --> 00:26:31,940
I've swapped out all our supplies

646
00:26:31,940 --> 00:26:33,810
for baby-safe alternatives.

647
00:26:33,980 --> 00:26:35,330
I made that myself.

648
00:26:35,420 --> 00:26:36,180
This spray

649
00:26:36,180 --> 00:26:37,460
is white vinegar and soap water.

650
00:26:37,460 --> 00:26:38,700
It's just for the bugs.

651
00:26:40,555 --> 00:26:41,980
It's fine. It's not toxic at all.

652
00:26:43,090 --> 00:26:44,290
That gave me such a scare.

653
00:26:45,700 --> 00:26:46,860
Looking at how

654
00:26:46,980 --> 00:26:48,330
panicked Le was just now,

655
00:26:49,140 --> 00:26:50,090
it seems like

656
00:26:50,460 --> 00:26:52,010
she really does care about this baby.

657
00:27:01,330 --> 00:27:02,220
Le.

658
00:27:03,490 --> 00:27:04,420
You're definitely

659
00:27:04,810 --> 00:27:06,530
going to be

660
00:27:06,810 --> 00:27:08,220
the best mother in the world.

661
00:27:14,330 --> 00:27:15,570
It looks like

662
00:27:15,660 --> 00:27:17,140
our family's only heir

663
00:27:18,090 --> 00:27:20,490
finally has an official status.

664
00:27:29,380 --> 00:27:30,810
Shu Jing, breakfast is ready.

665
00:27:33,810 --> 00:27:34,900
I've steamed those buns

666
00:27:34,900 --> 00:27:36,044
you were craving yesterday.

667
00:27:36,620 --> 00:27:37,860
I have to get going early today.

668
00:27:38,250 --> 00:27:39,010
I'm running late.

669
00:27:39,010 --> 00:27:40,619
But the kid isn't finished eating yet.

670
00:27:40,620 --> 00:27:41,530
Just eat on the way.

671
00:27:41,980 --> 00:27:42,810
Let's go.

672
00:27:44,460 --> 00:27:45,290
You...

673
00:28:07,530 --> 00:28:08,730
Are you okay?

674
00:28:08,860 --> 00:28:10,050
I'm fine.

675
00:28:12,620 --> 00:28:13,620
Here, have some water.

676
00:28:13,660 --> 00:28:14,570
Jing...

677
00:28:26,940 --> 00:28:27,860
Jing...

678
00:28:28,380 --> 00:28:30,250
How long did your morning sickness last?

679
00:28:30,700 --> 00:28:32,180
Fei didn't put me through too much.

680
00:28:32,290 --> 00:28:33,490
It only lasted about a month.

681
00:28:33,770 --> 00:28:34,900
I have a friend who was sick

682
00:28:34,900 --> 00:28:36,010
until she gave birth.

683
00:28:37,810 --> 00:28:39,490
Come on, don't scare me.

684
00:28:39,700 --> 00:28:41,250
I'm not. I'm being serious.

685
00:28:41,330 --> 00:28:42,330
You know what?

686
00:28:42,330 --> 00:28:43,940
I had quite a scare this morning.

687
00:28:44,090 --> 00:28:44,900
What happened?

688
00:28:45,050 --> 00:28:47,290
I thought I had accidentally inhaled

689
00:28:48,010 --> 00:28:49,140
some bug spray.

690
00:28:49,530 --> 00:28:51,050
I was terrified.

691
00:28:52,180 --> 00:28:53,810
But because of that incident,

692
00:28:54,330 --> 00:28:55,570
I realized

693
00:28:56,180 --> 00:28:57,810
that I actually do care about this baby.

694
00:28:57,810 --> 00:28:59,140
I really want to have him.

695
00:29:00,290 --> 00:29:01,420
Are you sure about this?

696
00:29:03,050 --> 00:29:04,620
Xiao Bing must be over the moon.

697
00:29:05,140 --> 00:29:06,460
He's absolutely thrilled.

698
00:29:12,140 --> 00:29:13,420
(Courtroom 3)

699
00:29:14,220 --> 00:29:17,980
(Court in Progress)

700
00:29:18,250 --> 00:29:20,490
(Family Court)
Why would I want black grout

701
00:29:21,180 --> 00:29:22,980
on my pristine white floor tiles?

702
00:29:23,140 --> 00:29:24,250
Doesn't it just look filthy?

703
00:29:24,250 --> 00:29:25,290
Even if they're white now,

704
00:29:25,290 --> 00:29:28,420
they'll get dirty after a few years
of wet mopping anyway.

705
00:29:28,420 --> 00:29:30,090
Pure black would look much better.

706
00:29:30,380 --> 00:29:31,380
Look, young man.

707
00:29:31,460 --> 00:29:32,460
Let's not keep bickering

708
00:29:32,460 --> 00:29:33,860
over such a minor detail.

709
00:29:33,860 --> 00:29:35,090
Is it really worth fighting

710
00:29:35,090 --> 00:29:36,420
over something like grout?

711
00:29:36,730 --> 00:29:38,570
It's not about the grout for me.

712
00:29:38,570 --> 00:29:40,420
It's about his attitude.

713
00:29:40,530 --> 00:29:41,666
When I brought it up,

714
00:29:41,733 --> 00:29:43,290
he started catching an attitude!

715
00:29:43,290 --> 00:29:44,620
How was I catching an attitude?

716
00:29:44,620 --> 00:29:45,810
What dirty looks?

717
00:29:45,940 --> 00:29:48,250
All I said was that I'm busy.

718
00:29:48,810 --> 00:29:50,330
Besides, it's less than a hundred yuan.

719
00:29:50,330 --> 00:29:51,940
It's already been delivered.

720
00:29:51,940 --> 00:29:53,200
We should just make do with it.

721
00:29:53,288 --> 00:29:54,050
This is a problem

722
00:29:54,050 --> 00:29:55,533
that could be fixed with a few clicks.

723
00:29:55,540 --> 00:29:56,810
If you want me to settle for this,

724
00:29:56,810 --> 00:29:57,450
what else do you

725
00:29:57,460 --> 00:29:58,770
expect me to make do with later?

726
00:29:58,770 --> 00:29:59,900
You're being unreasonable.

727
00:29:59,900 --> 00:30:00,700
This is ridiculous.

728
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:02,180
How am I being unreasonable?

729
00:30:02,460 --> 00:30:03,490
Let me ask you something.

730
00:30:03,490 --> 00:30:04,530
How many apartments

731
00:30:04,530 --> 00:30:06,290
in Tianhai City
can you afford in a lifetime?

732
00:30:06,300 --> 00:30:08,220
Maybe if we're lucky,
we'll upgrade in twenty years.

733
00:30:08,220 --> 00:30:09,822
But there's a good chance
we're stuck here.

734
00:30:09,866 --> 00:30:11,050
So why should I have to settle?

735
00:30:11,220 --> 00:30:12,180
All right, all right.

736
00:30:12,530 --> 00:30:13,980
Let's all take a second to calm down.

737
00:30:14,140 --> 00:30:16,660
It's perfectly normal for newlyweds

738
00:30:17,180 --> 00:30:18,290
to disagree

739
00:30:18,290 --> 00:30:19,570
while renovating their home.

740
00:30:19,860 --> 00:30:21,555
This doesn't count
as being unreasonable.

741
00:30:23,290 --> 00:30:24,380
But Plaintiff,

742
00:30:24,980 --> 00:30:25,940
there's a question here.

743
00:30:25,940 --> 00:30:28,180
I'm not sure
if you've really weighed it yet.

744
00:30:28,466 --> 00:30:30,755
A short, sharp pain
is better than a long, dull ache.

745
00:30:30,860 --> 00:30:31,900
So let's assume

746
00:30:32,090 --> 00:30:33,380
the short pain is truly brief

747
00:30:34,010 --> 00:30:35,555
and the long pain is truly eternal.

748
00:30:35,700 --> 00:30:36,955
Even then, have you considered

749
00:30:37,022 --> 00:30:38,330
the actual intensity of that pain?

750
00:30:38,810 --> 00:30:41,250
In medicine,
pain is ranked on a scale of one to ten.

751
00:30:41,860 --> 00:30:42,810
What if

752
00:30:43,380 --> 00:30:44,620
the short pain is a level ten,

753
00:30:45,290 --> 00:30:46,600
and it lasts for ten years?

754
00:30:47,700 --> 00:30:49,250
And the long pain is a level three,

755
00:30:49,250 --> 00:30:51,010
but it lasts for twenty?

756
00:30:51,730 --> 00:30:52,860
Which would you choose?

757
00:30:56,860 --> 00:30:58,330
Let me explain this to you.

758
00:30:58,530 --> 00:30:59,570
Level three pain is like

759
00:31:00,090 --> 00:31:01,620
the sensation of clapping your hands.

760
00:31:01,900 --> 00:31:03,090
But level nine pain?

761
00:31:03,530 --> 00:31:05,660
That's the feeling
of a third-degree burn.

762
00:31:05,860 --> 00:31:08,380
Your dermis and epidermis
are completely destroyed.

763
00:31:08,570 --> 00:31:10,940
It might even burn right through
to your muscle and bone.

764
00:31:12,530 --> 00:31:13,420
And then what?

765
00:31:13,530 --> 00:31:14,700
How do you know

766
00:31:14,810 --> 00:31:16,010
that divorce is a short pain?

767
00:31:16,180 --> 00:31:17,460
That a breakup is a short pain?

768
00:31:17,810 --> 00:31:19,220
Even if it is,

769
00:31:19,220 --> 00:31:20,490
have you thought about

770
00:31:20,490 --> 00:31:21,700
how agonizing it'll be?

771
00:31:21,770 --> 00:31:23,088
You're ripping a relationship

772
00:31:23,111 --> 00:31:24,420
completely out of someone's soul.

773
00:31:24,420 --> 00:31:26,180
How do you even rank that level of pain?

774
00:31:27,290 --> 00:31:28,530
In the beginning,

775
00:31:28,810 --> 00:31:30,290
you might think

776
00:31:30,660 --> 00:31:32,860
the wound will slowly heal with time.

777
00:31:33,330 --> 00:31:35,010
But you have no idea.

778
00:31:35,660 --> 00:31:37,940
A wound like that grows inward.

779
00:31:37,940 --> 00:31:39,900
It corrodes every cell in your body.

780
00:31:40,810 --> 00:31:42,420
It tears through every vein.

781
00:31:43,010 --> 00:31:44,810
It ties every nerve into knots.

782
00:31:45,570 --> 00:31:46,770
Maybe you'll never meet

783
00:31:46,770 --> 00:31:47,940
anyone like her again.

784
00:31:49,250 --> 00:31:51,010
Someone who can
make your heart skip a beat.

785
00:31:53,380 --> 00:31:54,530
Someone like her,

786
00:31:55,380 --> 00:31:56,730
who just smiles at you like that.

787
00:32:01,460 --> 00:32:03,220
And whenever anyone brings her up,

788
00:32:04,490 --> 00:32:06,140
you'll find yourself asking,

789
00:32:06,980 --> 00:32:08,940
"Why did I choose this?"

790
00:32:15,940 --> 00:32:19,820
(Heartbreak, pain, corrosion)

791
00:32:32,050 --> 00:32:32,980
My apologies.

792
00:32:33,570 --> 00:32:34,530
That analogy just now

793
00:32:34,530 --> 00:32:36,220
might've been a bit inaccurate.

794
00:32:36,380 --> 00:32:38,810
If anything I said felt inappropriate,

795
00:32:39,090 --> 00:32:40,380
please feel free to correct me.

796
00:32:44,330 --> 00:32:44,900
Right.

797
00:32:44,900 --> 00:32:45,940
Let's get back to

798
00:32:46,290 --> 00:32:47,420
this issue with the grout.

799
00:32:48,460 --> 00:32:49,700
Experts have pointed out...

800
00:32:49,810 --> 00:32:51,050
Judge, you can stop right there.

801
00:32:51,730 --> 00:32:52,860
I understand everything now.

802
00:32:54,770 --> 00:32:55,700
I don't want a divorce.

803
00:32:55,980 --> 00:32:56,860
Really?

804
00:33:02,290 --> 00:33:03,220
Yes.

805
00:33:03,660 --> 00:33:04,530
Thank you.

806
00:33:05,420 --> 00:33:07,380
Whether the pain is long
or short doesn't matter.

807
00:33:08,700 --> 00:33:09,810
The only thing that matters

808
00:33:09,810 --> 00:33:11,250
is that it still hurts.

809
00:33:12,770 --> 00:33:14,570
Instead of enduring that pain,

810
00:33:15,770 --> 00:33:18,180
I'd rather just cherish
the person in front of me.

811
00:33:20,730 --> 00:33:21,730
Honey,

812
00:33:21,980 --> 00:33:23,140
this was all my fault.

813
00:33:24,460 --> 00:33:26,490
I didn't respect your feelings.

814
00:33:27,330 --> 00:33:28,290
I'm so sorry.

815
00:33:32,180 --> 00:33:32,860
Okay.

816
00:33:32,860 --> 00:33:33,530
In that case,

817
00:33:33,770 --> 00:33:35,940
let's step out and prepare
a mediation agreement.

818
00:33:36,330 --> 00:33:37,220
Then, you can sign it.

819
00:33:37,420 --> 00:33:38,290
Sounds good.

820
00:33:50,180 --> 00:33:52,330
Has he always been a judge?

821
00:33:53,290 --> 00:33:54,980
Was he a doctor or something?

822
00:33:55,050 --> 00:33:56,250
How does he know so much?

823
00:33:57,290 --> 00:33:59,010
He's clearly done his research on pain.

824
00:33:59,810 --> 00:34:01,090
Is he a former anesthesiologist?

825
00:34:02,820 --> 00:34:05,740
(Heartbreak. Pain. Corrosion. Nerves.)

826
00:34:15,170 --> 00:34:16,170
Le!

827
00:34:16,170 --> 00:34:16,980
You startled me.

828
00:34:16,980 --> 00:34:17,940
Hey, look at this.

829
00:34:17,940 --> 00:34:19,860
Le's suddenly into a healthy lifestyle.

830
00:34:20,130 --> 00:34:21,530
She isn't even drinking cold water.

831
00:34:23,260 --> 00:34:24,170
And flat shoes!

832
00:34:24,170 --> 00:34:25,740
She's actually wearing flats.

833
00:34:26,130 --> 00:34:27,780
Our fierce office legend

834
00:34:27,780 --> 00:34:29,820
has turned into a proper lady.

835
00:34:30,300 --> 00:34:31,940
Le, did someone put a spell on you?

836
00:34:32,222 --> 00:34:33,490
- What's the deal?
- Hey, Le.

837
00:34:33,650 --> 00:34:34,570
What are you taking?

838
00:34:37,820 --> 00:34:39,210
Vitamin E.

839
00:34:40,780 --> 00:34:43,050
Wait, isn't that
for preventing miscarriages?

840
00:34:44,900 --> 00:34:45,940
No, it's not.

841
00:34:46,210 --> 00:34:47,460
My grandpa has Parkinson's,

842
00:34:47,740 --> 00:34:48,955
and he takes this medicine.

843
00:34:49,022 --> 00:34:50,940
He says it's for cardiovascular health.

844
00:34:51,650 --> 00:34:53,210
So, here's a thought.

845
00:34:53,260 --> 00:34:54,210
Scenario one,

846
00:34:54,300 --> 00:34:56,530
Le has early-onset Parkinson's.

847
00:34:56,740 --> 00:34:57,650
Scenario two,

848
00:34:57,740 --> 00:34:59,300
Le is pregnant.

849
00:34:59,650 --> 00:35:00,980
Which one do you guys think it is?

850
00:35:00,980 --> 00:35:01,940
Definitely scenario one.

851
00:35:01,940 --> 00:35:03,090
I'm going with one too.

852
00:35:03,740 --> 00:35:04,940
I'll take scenario two.

853
00:35:05,780 --> 00:35:06,860
I'll vote for one as well.

854
00:35:07,340 --> 00:35:08,260
You, too?

855
00:35:08,460 --> 00:35:10,170
Unbelievable. You're always chiming in.

856
00:35:10,170 --> 00:35:11,940
Don't start making fun of me.

857
00:35:13,300 --> 00:35:14,130
Can't I just take

858
00:35:14,130 --> 00:35:16,050
a simple vitamin supplement?

859
00:35:17,420 --> 00:35:19,530
You rub Vitamin E
on your dry hands, don't you?

860
00:35:19,530 --> 00:35:21,090
Do I go around saying you're sick

861
00:35:21,090 --> 00:35:23,940
and using heart meds
as a topical cream?

862
00:35:24,340 --> 00:35:25,130
Seriously.

863
00:35:25,130 --> 00:35:27,050
It's just that
you've changed so much lately.

864
00:35:27,050 --> 00:35:28,980
- Exactly.
- Totally.

865
00:35:28,980 --> 00:35:30,460
You're a different person, Le.

866
00:35:30,460 --> 00:35:32,340
You can't blame us for letting

867
00:35:32,340 --> 00:35:33,610
our imaginations run wild.

868
00:35:33,610 --> 00:35:35,170
Right?

869
00:35:36,530 --> 00:35:38,780
I agree.
You've been acting a bit forced lately.

870
00:35:38,860 --> 00:35:40,530
Are you hiding something from me?

871
00:35:42,460 --> 00:35:43,460
Jing is calling for you.

872
00:35:44,420 --> 00:35:46,130
(Court in Session)
Time is a cruel blade.

873
00:35:46,690 --> 00:35:47,690
I'm getting old.

874
00:35:47,955 --> 00:35:49,310
I've lost the support of my family.

875
00:35:50,260 --> 00:35:52,340
My husband hates everything I do,

876
00:35:52,530 --> 00:35:54,740
and even my kids won't take my side.

877
00:35:59,650 --> 00:36:01,490
You've been a couple for decades.

878
00:36:01,570 --> 00:36:04,010
It's normal to have
differences and conflicts.

879
00:36:04,690 --> 00:36:05,460
Why do you

880
00:36:05,460 --> 00:36:07,490
only see things
through such a negative lens?

881
00:36:08,780 --> 00:36:10,090
Besides, the defendant

882
00:36:10,090 --> 00:36:12,090
is making a real effort to talk to you.

883
00:36:13,090 --> 00:36:14,170
I don't entirely agree

884
00:36:14,170 --> 00:36:15,820
with what you said.

885
00:36:18,170 --> 00:36:19,570
Based on my experience,

886
00:36:20,010 --> 00:36:21,010
I feel that

887
00:36:21,260 --> 00:36:24,010
time is often more like a chisel.

888
00:36:29,100 --> 00:36:36,660
(Office. Meeting Room. Locker Room.)

889
00:36:40,040 --> 00:36:40,580
Hey.

890
00:36:40,860 --> 00:36:41,650
What's up?

891
00:36:41,650 --> 00:36:43,170
Have Hu cover for you tonight.

892
00:36:43,340 --> 00:36:44,650
Let's go out for dinner.

893
00:36:45,380 --> 00:36:46,650
What about Fei?

894
00:36:47,780 --> 00:36:48,690
Don't worry.

895
00:36:49,260 --> 00:36:50,740
I've got it all sorted out.

896
00:36:51,780 --> 00:36:54,420
We're going to that place
we've been meaning to try forever.

897
00:36:57,050 --> 00:36:58,050
Well,

898
00:36:58,300 --> 00:36:59,380
all right then.

899
00:36:59,820 --> 00:37:00,610
Tell you what.

900
00:37:00,610 --> 00:37:01,820
I'll come pick you up in a bit.

901
00:37:10,980 --> 00:37:12,300
Why on earth

902
00:37:12,300 --> 00:37:14,050
did we have to come
all the way out here?

903
00:37:14,340 --> 00:37:15,610
If you didn't want to stay home,

904
00:37:15,690 --> 00:37:17,333
we could've just gone
to the mutton shop.

905
00:37:17,333 --> 00:37:19,340
I could have had Hu pick things up,

906
00:37:19,420 --> 00:37:20,940
and we could've had a fresh meal there.

907
00:37:21,050 --> 00:37:22,010
Most importantly,

908
00:37:22,010 --> 00:37:24,170
I wouldn't have been late
to pick up Fei from school.

909
00:37:24,340 --> 00:37:25,780
How long has it been

910
00:37:25,780 --> 00:37:27,010
since we last ate out?

911
00:37:27,780 --> 00:37:29,530
Can't you just be romantic for once?

912
00:37:37,530 --> 00:37:39,420
I've already left Fei with Le.

913
00:37:39,820 --> 00:37:40,820
Stop worrying.

914
00:37:41,940 --> 00:37:42,940
If you ask me,

915
00:37:43,380 --> 00:37:44,380
this isn't romance.

916
00:37:44,610 --> 00:37:45,900
It's just a waste of money.

917
00:37:46,820 --> 00:37:47,530
By the way,

918
00:37:47,530 --> 00:37:49,610
don't keep bothering Le.

919
00:37:49,610 --> 00:37:51,340
She's got her own life to lead.

920
00:37:51,340 --> 00:37:53,210
Le really loves Fei.

921
00:37:53,420 --> 00:37:55,130
And Fei gets along with her just fine.

922
00:37:56,170 --> 00:37:58,210
Stop stressing and just eat your dinner.

923
00:38:12,570 --> 00:38:13,490
This meat is good.

924
00:38:14,740 --> 00:38:15,740
You can tell

925
00:38:15,860 --> 00:38:16,940
it's top-quality mutton.

926
00:38:17,740 --> 00:38:18,740
Here.

927
00:38:19,690 --> 00:38:21,530
Try some. It's really tasty.

928
00:38:25,690 --> 00:38:26,900
Do you remember

929
00:38:26,940 --> 00:38:28,650
when we first started dating?

930
00:38:28,650 --> 00:38:30,130
Whenever we worked late,

931
00:38:30,260 --> 00:38:31,610
we'd always go to that pizza place

932
00:38:31,610 --> 00:38:32,860
right outside the court.

933
00:38:33,490 --> 00:38:35,460
The pizza looked exactly like this one.

934
00:38:40,900 --> 00:38:43,260
I remember that shop owner

935
00:38:43,570 --> 00:38:44,820
so clearly.

936
00:38:45,940 --> 00:38:47,940
He knew you worked in the Family Court,

937
00:38:48,340 --> 00:38:49,980
so he'd specifically ask you for advice.

938
00:38:50,170 --> 00:38:52,460
He wanted to know
how to get his inheritance quickly,

939
00:38:52,780 --> 00:38:54,460
or how to keep it all for himself.

940
00:38:54,570 --> 00:38:56,490
What's going on in his head anyway?

941
00:38:57,690 --> 00:38:58,780
I remember that.

942
00:38:58,780 --> 00:38:59,820
Back then,

943
00:38:59,940 --> 00:39:02,650
we were just waiting for you, the judge
of the criminal division.

944
00:39:03,300 --> 00:39:04,210
I remember that day.

945
00:39:04,210 --> 00:39:05,690
The two of us were quite a team.

946
00:39:05,690 --> 00:39:06,650
We played off each other

947
00:39:06,650 --> 00:39:08,690
and gave that owner
a piece of our minds.

948
00:39:09,530 --> 00:39:11,490
Here is to a great partnership.

949
00:39:17,690 --> 00:39:19,340
It's amazing how fast time goes.

950
00:39:19,740 --> 00:39:20,860
In the blink of an eye,

951
00:39:20,860 --> 00:39:22,090
so many years have passed.

952
00:39:22,420 --> 00:39:23,530
Fei is already so grown up.

953
00:39:23,900 --> 00:39:24,820
She really is.

954
00:39:25,170 --> 00:39:27,010
If it hadn't been
for that incident with Tong,

955
00:39:27,740 --> 00:39:28,940
who knows?

956
00:39:29,210 --> 00:39:31,130
You might've been
a Chief Judge by now.

957
00:39:37,610 --> 00:39:38,570
Tell you what.

958
00:39:39,210 --> 00:39:40,170
When I get back,

959
00:39:40,460 --> 00:39:41,650
I'm going to study exactly how

960
00:39:41,780 --> 00:39:42,940
this dish is made.

961
00:39:43,177 --> 00:39:44,860
I'll add it as a new signature dish

962
00:39:45,090 --> 00:39:46,610
at our mutton soup shop.

963
00:39:46,610 --> 00:39:48,570
Then, today won't have been
a total waste.

964
00:39:56,820 --> 00:39:57,860
To be honest,

965
00:39:58,260 --> 00:39:59,900
I think it would be fine

966
00:40:00,170 --> 00:40:02,610
if you let Hu
and the others manage the shop.

967
00:40:04,340 --> 00:40:06,690
Would you consider
going for that interview again?

968
00:40:08,610 --> 00:40:09,530
I'm not going.

969
00:40:09,650 --> 00:40:11,111
I think things are great as they are.

970
00:40:11,380 --> 00:40:12,490
I can earn a living

971
00:40:12,740 --> 00:40:13,860
and still look after Fei.

972
00:40:14,050 --> 00:40:15,711
How exactly are you looking after her?

973
00:40:16,050 --> 00:40:18,530
You just pick her up from school
and bring her to the shop.

974
00:40:18,650 --> 00:40:20,170
You're so busy in the kitchen

975
00:40:20,555 --> 00:40:22,650
that you don't even know
where she's wandered off to.

976
00:40:22,820 --> 00:40:23,610
Sure.

977
00:40:23,780 --> 00:40:25,050
You always know where she is

978
00:40:25,650 --> 00:40:29,570
with all your GPS tracking
and surveillance cameras.

979
00:40:29,780 --> 00:40:31,490
But do you actually know what she likes?

980
00:40:32,490 --> 00:40:34,050
Do you know what she's afraid of?

981
00:40:35,690 --> 00:40:36,900
She's still little.

982
00:40:37,130 --> 00:40:38,980
She shouldn't be left alone.

983
00:40:39,690 --> 00:40:41,260
That's why I think this is for the best.

984
00:40:41,860 --> 00:40:43,460
I spend my days at the mutton soup shop,

985
00:40:43,460 --> 00:40:44,570
staying close to Fei.

986
00:40:44,570 --> 00:40:46,260
Living the simple things in life.

987
00:40:46,570 --> 00:40:47,490
It's perfect.

988
00:40:48,460 --> 00:40:50,090
How can you call this perfect?

989
00:40:51,490 --> 00:40:52,780
Is this really enough for you?

990
00:40:53,155 --> 00:40:54,570
Is this the extent of your ambition?

991
00:40:55,460 --> 00:40:56,740
What's wrong with my ambition?

992
00:40:57,380 --> 00:40:58,420
You're not happy?

993
00:40:58,940 --> 00:41:00,940
What are you going to do,
Chief Judge Shu?

994
00:41:01,090 --> 00:41:03,460
Are you going to enforce
a court order on me?

995
00:41:04,300 --> 00:41:05,940
You think you're being funny, don't you?

996
00:41:06,820 --> 00:41:08,820
Look at what you've turned into.

997
00:41:08,980 --> 00:41:10,530
I honestly can't talk to you anymore.

998
00:41:11,300 --> 00:41:13,460
All you care about is
that pathetic mutton soup shop.

999
00:41:13,866 --> 00:41:15,340
Do you even want to stay together?

1000
00:41:15,420 --> 00:41:17,980
Why wouldn't it work
because of the shop?

1001
00:41:18,650 --> 00:41:20,466
If you're done with us,
then just say so.

1002
00:41:26,570 --> 00:41:28,300
What's that supposed to mean?

1003
00:41:30,130 --> 00:41:31,210
It doesn't mean anything.

1004
00:41:31,420 --> 00:41:32,460
You're the one who said

1005
00:41:33,170 --> 00:41:34,210
we can't do this anymore.

1006
00:41:34,420 --> 00:41:35,690
So let's just stop.

1007
00:41:39,010 --> 00:41:40,170
Let's go our separate ways.

1008
00:41:58,570 --> 00:41:59,780
I'm going to pick up Fei.

1009
00:42:00,511 --> 00:42:02,133
She won't sleep well in a strange bed.

1010
00:42:39,690 --> 00:42:40,530
Oh, you're awake?

1011
00:42:40,690 --> 00:42:42,300
Come over here and have some breakfast.

1012
00:42:42,780 --> 00:42:44,260
Grandma sent these biscuits.

1013
00:42:44,490 --> 00:42:46,820
I made them with lard and
preserved greens. They're great.

1014
00:42:48,860 --> 00:42:49,860
What time is it?

1015
00:42:51,422 --> 00:42:54,022
(Meeting Minutes, Copy)
Shouldn't you be on the train by now?

1016
00:42:54,140 --> 00:42:54,900
(Client List)

1017
00:42:54,900 --> 00:42:56,860
I woke up too early.
I'm going back to sleep.

1018
00:42:58,780 --> 00:42:59,690
It's seven o'clock.

1019
00:42:59,980 --> 00:43:01,610
I only got up

1020
00:43:01,780 --> 00:43:02,980
to enjoy a nice breakfast.

1021
00:43:02,980 --> 00:43:04,010
Come and have some, too.

1022
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

1023
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

1024
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

1025
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1026
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1027
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1028
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

1029
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

1030
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

1031
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

1032
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

1033
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1034
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1035
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1036
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

1037
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

1038
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

1039
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

1040
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

1041
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

1042
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

1043
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

1044
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

1045
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

1046
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

1047
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:44,590
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1048
00:44:44,590 --> 00:44:47,040
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1049
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:49,150
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1050
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:51,530
♪Some questions♪

1051
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,800
♪Weigh like mountains♪

1052
00:44:57,690 --> 00:45:02,840
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1053
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:07,130
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1054
00:45:07,310 --> 00:45:12,360
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1055
00:45:12,730 --> 00:45:16,430
♪Where fairness stands♪

1056
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:19,680
♪Within the law♪

1057
00:45:20,840 --> 00:45:29,520
♪And within every heart♪
